All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Action
The Action class represents an action in a Function-as-a-Service (FaaS) architecture.
ActionProxyImpl
The ActionProxyImpl class provides implementations of methods defined in the IActionProxy interface.
BigGroup
The BigGroup class represents a resource policy for selecting invokers to execute actions in big groups.
Controller
The Controller class manages the invocation of actions in a Function-as-a-Service (FaaS) environment.
CountWords
The CountWords class provides a method to count the number of words in a list of strings.
DynamicProxy
The DynamicProxy class implements the InvocationHandler interface to provide dynamic proxy behavior.
GreedyGroup
The GreedyGroup class represents a resource policy for selecting invokers to execute actions in a greedy manner.
IActionProxy
The IActionProxy interface represents an action proxy.
Invoker
The Invoker class represents an invoker in the Function-as-a-Service (FaaS) environment.
MemoizationDecorator<T,R>
The MemoizationDecorator class provides a way to memoize the results of a function.
Metric
The Metric class represents a metric recorded during the execution of an action.
MetricsSummary
The MetricsSummary class represents a summary of metrics collected during the execution of actions.
Observer
The Observer interface represents an observer that receives updates from subjects.
PolicyManager
The PolicyManager class manages resource policies for selecting invokers.
Reduce
The Reduce class provides methods for reducing word counts and total word counts.
ResourcePolicy
The ResourcePolicy interface represents a policy for selecting invokers to execute actions.
RoundRobin
The RoundRobin class represents a resource policy for selecting invokers in a round-robin fashion.
